Chilean Stocks: Electrica Pilmaiquen and Sudamericana de Vapores

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-12-12T14:30:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-12/chilean-stocks-electrica-pilmaiquen-and-sudamericana-de-vapores.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:11 a.m. in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index fell 0.9 percent to 4,146.08. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated 1.7 percent to 2,269.27.  Cia. Sudamericana de Vapores SA (VAPORES)   lost 3.6
percent to 107 pesos, a record low.  Latin America ’s largest
container shipping company announced Dec. 9 it plans to sell
5.87 billion new shares at 20.45 cents or 104 pesos each to help
shore up its finances.  Empresa Electrica Pilmaiquen (PILMAIQ)  SA rose 1.5
percent to 2,100 pesos, its seventh day of gains and with volume
more than six times the average of the last three months. The
power generator has called for an extraordinary shareholder vote
for Dec. 23 to elect a new board after a petition from those who
own more than 10 percent of the company’s stock, according to a
statement published Dec. 7 on the website of the Santiago stock
exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
